From bbb org

Date of Action: 11\/27\/2013 

On November 27, 2013, the Arizona Attorney General filed a Consent Judgment against ... Gilbert Fletcher's Tire and Auto Service violated the Arizona Consumer Fraud Act by performing and charging for unnecessary repairs to the State's undercover vehicle, charging for parts that were not replaced, and performing some services prior to receiving consent..

... ...pay the State $20,000 in civil penalties, $8, 265.63 in costs, attorney's fees, and restitution. In addition, Fletcher's Tire and Auto Service, as a whole, agreed to voluntarily implement a secret shopping program at each location to monitor and prevent deceptive practices and report the results periodically to the Attorney General's Office.

New cafe.... Previously occupied by Cafe Ted... Scheduled to open sometimes later this month... (February). According to their Facebook page, Emily's cafe will be open on March 6 with a soft opening...
Everything is good and the staff is also super nice and friendly...they really give fast food a food name! My favorite are the bowls...
I honestly think that their burgers are better than In N Out....everything tastes fresher and the burgers are bigger. The burger in a lettuce wrap is a must try if you haven't tried it yet.
Barista cashier not very friendly...
Enjoying a French breakfast !
Great macarons, chocolates, pastries and gelato....
Best chocolates, macarons and gelato.....
Like everything about this place, especially the owners!
Great lunch spot!
Delicious gelato, pastries and more....
Great teas, espresso and cappuccino along with lovely sweets ...
Love everything about this place.....
Very friendly staff! Great simple and delicious lunch........
Quaint coffee shop!
Delicious pies and coffee....
Love this place !
Excellent baristas!
Dog friendly patio...
I ordered the tuna sandwich,it was fresh and delicious and the arugula was a pleasant addition to a classic tuna,I would have enjoyed a little more of the actual protein..overall delicious.
It was great and I highly recommend the Sonny Boy for dinner.
If you're just joining us, welcome to our culinary campaign. Really enjoyed Sacks' Encore with hot peppers and feta yogurt dressing.
Great breakfast actually. I strongly recommend the Oatmeal and Jalapeño Quiche.
Traditional bacon and eggs. It was delicious and comes with a side of fruit. Always a good place for a quick, cheap, tasty meal.
Pork Chile Verde with Corn Bread. Wow. Think I need a nap now. Probably walk it off today knocking on doors.

Spoke to Joel, part owner of Maizies and father of Maizie, and they are making a big push to drive people here for breakfast Monday - Sunday now. We stopped in for lunch and I had the Sonoran Chicken Panini with cottage cheese. Very tasty! Please stop by for breakfast.

As promised to Maizie, the owner, I came for breakfast. She just started a Monday - Friday breakfast starting at 7:30 am. Please come in and help her get her breakfast business off the ground! The Classic on Central is always a good choice.
At Pink Spot Coffee and Ice Cream, started with a mint chip ice cream cone, but couldn't resist and had to order a cappuccino as well. Great local neighborhood spot. Stop by sometime.
We started with chips and salsa and guacamole. After I had four Carne Asada tacos with pico de gallo and extra spicy hot sauce. It was really good and the tea is fresh brewed and delicious as well.
Started with Artichoke Heaven and then finished with Acapulco Cheesesteak. So full, but worth every bite!
Ordered the Gringo with steak. So good. Their chips and salsa is homemade and fresh brewed iced tea!
Had the chicken breast spring rolls. Try we're great with the peanut sauce and chilli paste, but my favorite thing was the edamame.
Had the Grilled Chicken Sandwich with mango and jalapeño relish. It was great, but the Deviled Egg Dip & Chips were Outstanding!
My campaign manager and I split the Phoenix and Carne Asada. A lot of beef and hot peppers on a fresh cooked roll. The french fries are amazing. So good, but I am so full right now!

Just had the guajillo short rib and pork green chile enchilada. Wow! They were amazing I had them with the "Christmas" sauce which is a combination of red and green sauce. Also had the lava salsa which I thought was perfect, but Patricio (name stuck after last night), thought it was really spicy. Hope to take our friends to try someday.
Had the Pesto Turkey Sandwich with a side salad. It was delicious and Jonathan brought over homemade cookies after the meal. Good luck Jonathan and Brian with your new endeavor!
Enjoying sloppy Joe and an Ice Tea to add another restaurant to our culinary campaign! A must go if you haven't been.
All time favorite: fresh Mozz\/tomato\/ basil sandwich

Miso ramen is a HUGE delicious shar-able portion. 

Sushi is fair but at least not overpriced. 

Rice bowl w\/tuna sashimi = 2 thumbs up. 

Wish i had the mango lemonade recipe, very tasty, would buy this again.

Also, bird toothpick dispenser is the best I've seen. You gotta try it.

Dessert is the best part!
Strawberry cheesecake :)
Nice ambiance!
excellent!

BEST Mexican food in town!
Great service, beautiful interior. 
Highly recommend:
Appetizer: guacamole & chips
Entrée: Enchilada verdes, Beef tacos (forgot the actual name on the menu)
Dessert: flan--MmMmmmm (even if your full from eating every morsel of delicious food....MUST get, so worth it)
Drink: any of the agua frescas
AUTHENTIC...
LOVE the rice.
LOVE that they don't drown the food in American-type cheeses.
New hotel restraunt that has replaced Gallo is faster, w tastier more authentic food\/salsas...
Get mini corn dogs! Great to share.
Fun place, great music, very laid back\/casual

Good rolls & selection for the price! Not "top notch" sushi but if you are looking for that don't expect to pay $5 per roll!! 

Our best combo: 
1)Wrap: soy paper
2)rice: brown
3)Protein: salmon
4)Veggies\/fruits (3): sprouts, tofu skin, STRAWBERRIES(!) 
5)Sauce: sweet chile 
Pleasantly surprised by all our random combos but this was our fave.

Campari tomatoes are tasty but slightly overpriced for the amount; for 2 ppl to share, 3 at most. 

Big Star pizza is a perfect mix of meat n veggies. Filling n yummy. Appropriately priced. 

Lil triple dessert is for chocolate lovers...mmmmmmm.

Coolers are pricey for the volume but delicious & good % etoh (for a lightweight)

Atmosphere is nice & relaxed. Will return :)
Best part of this place = games & cocktails...food is average. Pretzel appetizer is good as are all the grilled veggies (appetizers)

Wow.
Best. Place. Ever.

So far number 1 spot this summer for a COLD treat & BOBA TEA!!! (I tried Taro milk tea)
Vodka sweet tea....refreshing.
Good location, prices & sushi!

BEST PIZZA IN PHOENIX!!!!!
Would def come back. 

Had the POMO classica pizza--perfection!
Cocktails: recommend the Vespa 
Dessert: forgot the name but has figs in it...mmmmm I'd buy a whole block if I could. 

TEN STARS, easily.

Food just as good as in any chick fil a, expected.  Location is convenient but VERY poor planning in terms of drive-thru situation, parking. I love that it's close to home but many will opt to go elsewhere just due to the traffic situation alone--really, a drive through line directed towards the Sports authority parking lot?? Also, management should have thought to place experienced ppl at this locale to open & get things settled while  training new employees at established locations.Just saying

Great food & tasty $3 margarita!!!!!

Carne Asada torta FIVE stars
Kale & Quinoa salad---good but if you are very hungry won't be filling enough without adding protein. 
Guac is tasty & good portion size -has a basil\/tomato twist but a bit over priced (ie it basically costs the same as an entree)
Margarita was yummy, only $3, perfect strength (not weak or overdone)
Great outdoor seating
Like the music
Friendly & attentive staff:)
Tomato mozzarella sandwich is my favorite.
Clean, good smoothies and yummy sandwiches!
Such amazing organic, vegetarian and vegan options!
Here for the clothing swap event
I drive 30 minutes out of my way to shop here!
You can rent yoga mats and hand towels for $1!
Wish they played music in the waiting area for the classes.
Great honey vanilla latte!
If you reserve a table on yelp, they will honor it at this establishment. Yippee!
Don't buy a salad here. Stick to a burger and fries.
Great fries!
Food quality has gone down. My breakfast burrito was burnt to a crisp on the bottom.
Christmas shopping!
Pretty hoppin' on a Wednesday night!
When the weather is nice, watch out for zero seating space and a line out the door on Saturdays. Even at 1:30 in the afternoon it's standing room only.
Really fast drive thru and their open late!
Not too busy at lunch time on a weekday

Accidentally left my purse here overnight- I called in the morning and sure enough they still had it! I picked it up but they refused a tip, saying "Just come back and eat with us again". Thank you pizza people pub for keeping my purse and wallet safe and for being classy people!
Def try their antipasto, DELISH!
Best shrimp pad Thai & cha shu ramen! Prices Super reasonable too

I had the New York on a kisser roll, it has s nice portion of coleslaw, I asked to sub the French fries for their macaroni salad. Sandwich was delicious plenty moist pastrami and tasty coleslaw. The macaroni salad I did not care, tasted too much the sweet pickle relish. Price was about $9, bit pricey for sandwich but very satisfying:)

Love this place, food is DELISH and portions leave you full and content! Had a gyro pita with French fries, need to say more? I can only get this tastyness when around this area, I so wish we had one closer to Buckeye!
So tasty, juicy meat not greasy or fried dry beef here!
Quick friendly service with pharmacy!

PLEASE make sure you check they charge the right $ amount for what you get! Carne asada, tasteless-liver taste, soda was flat!So sad, it's used to be delish, as so many business once they open a few more food quality goes down!

Hot pastrami with mustard sliced pickles and cheese(provolone?) 7.99. Bottle soda 1.99, total+ tax $10.81 BUT no other good Italian sandwich place around, plus you can get some Italian meats to take home if you got the $.

Wow! We have one hidden gem here! Taking home a pumpkin loaf $5, an almond horn and eclair, $10..but pricey but if you are in the area and want grandma's style bake treats this is your place;) oh yes, it's closed on Mondays.

Got the Sunny boy pizza ($18)and Spiedini($10), pretty tasty! And yes as delicious as it was, I definatly feel that you can get same quality and tasty pizza at CIBO'S and half the wait d price;-) P.S. one pizza is plenty for 2 adults:)
My definetly favorite for breakfast gotta try Biscuits and Chorizo Gravy!

What better place than Lux to have a late starter breakfast with hubby! Had a slice of blueberry pear almond cake, just the perfect sweetness. I also got a cafe au laitte with almond milk, PERFECTO! Hubby had an egg sandwich, he gives it a 8 only because it was a bit messy,lol.. ALREADY planning my next mission: Jalapeño Mac & cheese! I'll be back baby :p
What can I say, good coffee,good music & good eats, can't beat it!

This has been long time over due, we came on a mission: jalapeno and bacon Mac& cheese and the NY strip steak..drum roll please...EXCELLENT! I highly recommend it. The strip was juicy, tender and perfectly cooked-pink but not too over done, it was served with a side of tasty roasted garlicky red potatoes and green beans with bacon! The Mac & cheese-DLISH!In my husband's words "they were not messing around with the Jalapeño! Oh yes, hubby and I shared the steak and mac and it was perfect portion.
Wether it's an early bird morning or a late owl's night Lux's tasty goodies never dissapoints! Had a velvet latte with almond milk and slice peach crumble pie,  TAAASTY :)
Always, very pleased;)
Jalapeño and bacon mac & cheese, love it! You will not be disappointed trust me;) I don't eat mac n cheese anywhere else (don't even make it at home couse don't care for it) except here of course B-)

So I came to my #1 favorite coffee hang out place @ Lux to celebrate new job\/career..I always get my coffee just how me likes!lol BUT this time I hate to say I got my barista in a not so happy to see me mood by ordering a 6 shot expresso velvet drink! I get his point, I do,that much expresso can be bad for your health\/heart...but like he said and like it or not they have it on the menu...plus this might be my first and last time ordering it..after his little I can care less attitude!

I was in the area and haven't had lunch soo... (you guess it!) Gotta get me some of their Dlish mac & cheese with bacon and Jalapeño!! Thank goodness is Friday and I feel I'm in cloud 9 with my bowl of comfort goodness and a refreshing Boylan grape soda!

Decided to give their hot a chocolate a try, I ordered it with almond milk and it was ok nothing fancy or impressive but it was tasty probably because it's made with Ghirardelly chocolate..also had their almond oatmeal whoopee pie and if you been here before you'll probably agree that their bake goods are never disappointing-yummers!:)
After a wonderful dinner a nice, time to enjoy my favorite spot for a great cup of coffee and dessert:) what can I say life is good!
Hubby had their biscuits n chorizo gravy, which were rich and scrumptious tasting! I had their sweet Dutch pancake with fresh berries and cream and side of bacon, so delish!

Awesome rustic pizza, we had the Tartufata: which had truffle oil, mozzarella and prosciutto, LOVE IT! It had a wonderful buttery taste that went great with crust..Second pizza was Capricciosa also very tasty: had artichokes, ham, black olives, mozzarella...Although waitress said each pizza was individual serving, I disagree, size was perfect about 3 slices each for two adults!

I had the Grilled pork with spring roll, it was quite tasty but they have changed the meat portion pieces now are a lot smaller and grill flavor-that I used to love is not as strong :( The egg roll was also tasty but again portion size is smaller. I also had a Thai tea and today it was kinda too assert and not enough tea flavor. But don't get me wrong taste wise was al yummy :)
I was expecting the Shawarma to be in a freshly baked pita
Had a breakfast sausage sandwich since I asked for no cheese on mine flavor wise was good but sandwich itself was bit too dry-cibara bread was too thick :(
Can always count with cheaper gas here!
I like that if I say extra crispy fries, I get extra crispy fries! I also like that their dipping sources are self serve, they're not being stingy by rationing them, Thank you :)
Nutty cookie gnar gnar with almond milk,YUM!

Delish drink but only thing is the price:( I got a small is $4.85but with almond drink $6.11! For a small drink,Yikes! Come on, how about charging 50-75¢? I can't help to think that I'm been taken advantage off  since it's one of two places in west valley with an alternative and since Starbucks does not do almond milk..(other place is Dutch Bros on Thunderbird off the 101, they don't charge extra for making my drinks with coconut milk!).
My love brought me to dinner and ordered for me the lobster tail with rib eye steak! Delish! Cooked to perfection and quite a portion to leave you completely satisfied;)

Sweet deals, I like that they brought back clearance, coupons and good sale prices! Arizona brand $11.99 shorts & $16.99 St. Johns brand shorts for him, can't beat it! Plus they emailed a $10.00 off coupon on purchase over 50dlls, see what I mean?!

So I'm driving home, getting the hunger pains when I pass a sign for PHO&BOBA...Now, being from sunny CA I know that where ever they have Pho and boba, I shall find some Vermicelli too! So I made U turn and boy am I glad I did! Had the Vermicelli with grill tasty sweet pork,YUM! and for my drive home with a smile I got a Thai tea,oh yes sweet and Delicious! From what I could observe their PHO is highly requested, guess that will be my next bowl of tastyness, can't wait to bring hubby on Friday!

I'm back for some PHO! lol, and was not disappointed! Hubby got the Pho with eye round steak and I got the ox tail! So very dlish! After having tried their Vermicelli, Thai tea and now their Pho, I'm makin this my favorite Vietnamese restaurant PHO sure!

Love this place! Not in the mood for Pho? There's plenty choices here...I Stopped by and got their grill pork with broken rice and Thai tea=YUM! It's served with a small side of clear broth, also delish:) I only Wish they had served me a bit more of their tasty grill pork! By the way, server informed me they started making Thai tea in house, very pleased:)

After walking around and sweating off about 2lbs at ultimate consignment..it was def time for some cold Thai tea with BOBA! And of course, I could not pass the opportunity of enjoying a delish grill pork Vermicelli!
Never fails to leave me completely satisfied and smiling!

I'm soo hooked on this place...and since today is the first day it feels to me like actual fall ( 6:30pm temps in high 60s) it's def time to switch from Vermicelli salad for some Pho.. and this place is #1 in the west valley due to their food tasting more traditional than a chain restaurant..I got the ox tail soup and I love it! Tip, make sure you do like and have eaten ox tail before or it will be a bit intimidating
Ahh man! That was Disappointing, their dirty chai used to be good, what happened? :( No chai flavor with only water down coffee flavor.

Hubby and I been faithful followers in all of their 3 relocations so I know this place had great ambience and expresso drinks..but today I was out of luck, wanted a Himalayan hammer which is chai and expresso but they were out of chai:( So to cheer me up I ordered their Cubano, condense milk and expresso made with almond milk...WOW, COFFEE LOVERS BE WARE IT WAS SUPER STRONG! But I liked it ;-)
I love sprouts, great prices on better for your health food! Not everything in the store is organic but I know I'm not gettin mega corn syrup, processed and fillers either!
Yummy! Nice way to finish up the holiday weekend!
I love the chicken salad bowl I get my protein and veggies all tasty without the fatty fried thou:)
I need the exit from freeway open!
Gotta have some carne asada for lunch, I so wish they had better parking... but after eating my burrito some how parking doesn't bother me as much,haha!!
Like I said, I find the food and staff way better here than that of 7th Ave...so this is my favorite for carne asada and tamarind drink after long day at work!
Gotta have cinnamon roll when I come here, hot freshly baked and plenty frosting!

Hubby and I heard great reviews from this place and don't get me wrong is good but I felt it didn't live up to expectations this is why: I ordered the bacon and mushroom omelet it could of been tastier, lacking bacon and the mushrooms? Well this was the let down, they seemed to be canned mushrooms:( Hubby had their Santa Fe eggs Benedict and he said that they were tasty the biscuits and sauce were good. I also had the Italian roast coffee- I really enjoyed with their cinnamon roll.

If you ask me, this food quality and taste of dishes here beats Barrio cafe hands down (was so disappointed last time I was there:[) We started with chicharon, then shared the ribeye tacos, shrimp tacos, ribeye burrito and flan! ALL WAS AMAZING! Service was also wonderful, keep it up:)
YUM!
Kipling for a yummy breakfast late in the day? You come to right place! Had their Steak (5oz) and 2 eggs served with their guacamole, pinto beans and 3 3"tortillas,TASTY! All $16!
2 words: Lettuce wraps! By the way they have 3 different types, traditional, spicy Korean and Thai chicken,Yum! Only $6.95:)
Always check their 98¢ produce, always a good buy!
Monday thru Saturday only!

The kalby dolsot bibim bab rib meat in a super hot ceramic bowl was SO VERY Flavorful! Also had the pork belly, this needs bit more flavor and was bit too dry, although with all the side dishes they enhance the flavor:) Over all including the service we were very satisfied!
The corn with cheese is the bomb.  Do not be afraid to get messy.  One of the best carne asada burrito in az

How much do we really like the ramen soups here? Well, let me just share that hubby and I don't think twice about the drive we do coming here from Buckeye! And yes, we have discovered and really like Cherry Blossom's ramen too BUT we are not too pleased with their noodle and meat portions..I DEFINETLY recommend you try their Tomkatsu, and Almond milk tea..And if you don't mind left overs, then place an extra order of noodles to go so that you can have them the next day with your left over broth.

In the mood for some spicy ramen, tried Tokyo ramen original with pork :) hit the spot! I know, I know, this probably is not even close to what's the real deal cooked up in Japan or an authentic Japanese kitchen but then again we are in the middle of a desert no where near a Japanese cultural community & in this case it hits the spot every time B-)

Ay mama! This was pretty tasty! Had a carne asada burrito ($4.50) which I was so very pleased to see it had only onions, avocado, cilantro, prefect! I also had a taco de lengua ($1.25)also tasty meat, only thing maybe a bit more meat ;-) P.S. Don't be scare off with how it looks and make sure your not going into tire shop instead,lol!

I tried to stay focus and make it home but I was betrayed by my taste buds cravings and stomach! And so, I made a detour to tacos Atoyac!lol.. I been here before, so I knew a carne asada burrito with a Jarrito would hit the spot, and so it was! Nice hot for tortilla, filled with only support flavorful carne asada, onions & cilantro, they serve on side the guacamole and choice of salsa plus some grilled onions and Jalapeño..YUM..and it will cost you about $5 and some change, can't go wrong:p
If you are looking for traditional Vietnamese Flavors then this is not for you :( I had high expectations for it and sadly it didn't impress me much..
Gotta LOVE their $2, 6"cold cut sandwich, great price!

If your hungry, want a tasty sandwich and don't want to get stuffed? 3 words: get their mini! Don't be fooled by their name "mini"  bread size & with all their filings, I say pretty close to a 6"from subway:) I got the famous Italian, dlish! Just keep an eye on then, they can get carry away with salt\/pepper, oil and vinegar ;-)

Hubby had cubano, he liked but not sweet enough..I had Italian sodas which I'm used to having heavy cream, flavor syrup and mineral water, in here was just the water n syrup for$2.50--sad to say they where not so great :-(
Thai tea is tasty, boba is soft but could be sweeter,friendly sevice..Closest boba place to home in Buckeye so will do on hot days cravings ;-)
I recommend coming when temps are in lower 80's, they have water coolers but still pretty hot;)

Had the banana bread pudding French toast with side if sausage, 2 thick and Delish bread pudding squares so very moist, the sausage was not your typical sausage more like old fashion casing but very good! Overall everything was superb, only drawback was that the bread pudding was more on the cold side than warm and for a breakfast dish I would prefer it to be hot, otherwise makes great dessert. PS the caramel sauce it comes with bread pudding its SUPER rich get on the side..
had the three sister strata and bmoc amazing presentation and taste!

My hubby was in the mood for Portuguese doughnut, once here couldn't resist trying another scrumptious dish of theirs.. Mexican Benedict, plenty of the hollandaise sauce and chorizo on it very rich and tasty. I got the piperrada which was served with plenty of fry pork shoulder,sauteed onions red and green bell peppers topped with 2 eggs and served with 2 slices of toast. It was yummy but it needed some kind of sauce...

Yup, found some waffle and bacon here, pretty tasty too! Dishes here unique but tasty. However, if you are in a mood for more traditional breakfast, I  recommend hitting another establishment near by, like Matt's Big Breakfast (good 'ol pancakes, eggs and hashbrwns).
Always fun & delish!
Trust me, Can't go wrong with the simple but Dlish Almond Milk Tea :)
Thai tea BOBA tea! Yum! Perfect to cool off!
On a HOT Sat afternoon sweet almond milk tea drink with boba perfect way to cool down!

This morning woke up with tastebuds screaming: we want BACON! What better way to start the day than having breakfast at Matt's?..I know you're probably saying "good luck with wait time" but the stars are aligned it's your day and you just know it!lol , when I enquired we were told our wait time was maybe 30mnts, so I decided to waited out because if you being to Matt's you know that's nothing, and sure enough in 30 mnts we were taken to our table! See the pic? I certainly was not disappointed!

Hubby and I stopped by wanting some tasty light food and drinks to cool off on this insane 118° weather..The Verdict? the milk tea drinks flavor(coconut and almond milk tea) were the BOMB!The boba was soft but too plain, they need to leave it longer on the syrup,their shrimp fried rice was ok but it was a bit tuff\/uncooked and needed bit more seasoning..We also had the popcorn chicken-very tasty and spicy-live it! Over all I give it an 8, and I yes I will be back, cause I see them improving
I love you have plenty choices with lactose free snows, milk teas, smoothies and Vietnamese coffee drinks!
On the way to work and after a stressful event.... this treat is just right to help make any crazy day better! (Popcorn chicken $3.45, Boba drink $3.25)

Hubby and I were super excited to check out this place but close to 1hr later and our food order is no show! Did I mentioned this is our second visit? Yup first visit they had no Vietnamese sandwich bread? Come on making it super hard to give good rating :(
One word: dlish! You will not be disdained with their almond milk tea, and their boba shoddy and sweet! Next time will give their yogurt a try ;)

I saw the cafe on Good Morning Az, it's right next to the farmers market. They renovated it quite nice. It's an open floor plan, inside I wish they had bit more sitting & tables to eat because its sitting area is more for lounging. They also have a roomy patio that's connected to their inside bar...I got fresh oj-yummy, and the frittata with egg whites-it had sauteed red bell peppers, onions, fresh arugula, tomatoes,pesto and a slice of nicely butter French bread-yummy!Great for big groups:)

After having a tasty dinner at Short Leash hotdogs my taste buds wanted something sweet (I know Pie Hole is next door but not in mood for pie)...found it at MELT! Had their strawberry ice cream, my hubby got super farm: chocolate hazelnuts and nutella! We met the friendly owner who was working the late shift and who has a 9month old at home, you go Crystal! Def will visit again:)

Chicago style hotdogs? Not so sure how authentic they are here but I was pleased with all beef dog topped with sweet relish, tomatoes,onions, mustard and a nice pickle spear on a poppy seed bun..and even though it was tasty I did not find it that exceptional to convince me to do the drive.
The bread is baked in brick oven fresh. Can't beat it. Mozzarella sandwich is always good.
You can't have anything bad here. Everything is premium 100% in your mouth yums
They finally have power outlets again.
Pistachio ice creeeeeeam!!
The tropical is best of the iced teas. And you get one free refill. Time for mine!
Wifi has been acting up (more than usual) the past 2 days.
Iced tea is one free refill! Tropical is tastiest.
Check out the goat
Great place to study. Large table to lay out your work. Four different rooms.
Iced coffee is tops. I think it has a shot of espresso
Mac and cheese is tops!

Lux is huge! Great for working on stuff if you're a student or a teacher. However, it's mostly (but not all) communal tables, so not good for more private convos\/dates. This is one of the four rooms.
The flatbreads are basically a personal pizza. And they're amazing.
Happy hour menu is pretty great. The potato fingerlings (pictured) are good to share and the flatbreads are basically a full personal pizza.
My personal recommendation if you're unsure: Pick Two with Chicken Pesto sandwich and Potato Cream Cheese soup
The egg torta is the best.
Is NOT open evenings\/nights on weekdays and is CLOSED on weekends. Great pour over coffees tho!
It's all about the Big John (easy mayo).
The BMOC is pretty big compared to the other entrees. It was a very interesting mixture of sweet and some salty. Quite unique.
Get the chicken sandwich. It's good. Haaaaahahahaha
They are slow if they have only one person in the kitchen. If you call in an order, add about 10 min to their guesstimation.
Try the biscochitos (Mexican wedding cookies)!! Reeeeally good and crumbly.
Try the Rosa. The onion and the pistachio combination was surprisingly tasty.
Ask for a casita instead of a room. They're more private, pretty sweet and close to the pools.
You can't go wrong ordering the chorizo omelette. Ask for extra salsa too!
Live music on Saturday nights
Add avocado to the Dilly Club, you won't be disappointed.
If you have questions, find the guy with the top hat. He's very helpful
Head here for the 4th of July fireworks show.
Validate AZ center parking in the lobby.
Lots of things to keep the kids busy while the adults play in the slots area
Ask for an east side room facing the Encore and you won't hear the train whistle while you're trying to get some shut-eye.
If you've got kids, ask them to double cut your pie and they'll oblige!
Great service and food. Staff is friendly.
You can't beat the Red Velvet!
The custom order cakes are a hit with my daughters. Choose your theme, two flavors and Scooptacular will do the rest!
I got the Fat Elvis sundae but was eyeing the girls' S'mores sundae the entire time.
Get there early and wear your yoga pants.
I would wait a while. They are still learning how to wrap burritos.
Don't let the long lines fool you.  It moves quickly.
Their bread is amazing!
Just had meatballs with delicious marinara and stewed tomatoes! Sooo good. For dessert try the vanilla rice pudding its amazing!
Amazing shrimp dumplings! (Everything here is delicious!)
Everything here is amazing!
Awesome happy hour! Good assortment of items and good $$.  And of course amazing regular menu! Me & my husband love all of their food here!!
Try their dynamite salnon roll from the happy hour. It rocks!
We love the food! Great sushi and good prices!
Really good miso soup!
Eattting diner at this place right now and omg the pot stickers are amazing!! Try them.
Amazing pot stickers try them!
Very good food. The prices can be high. But very good German food and beer.
Try the grape leaves they r really good and delicious!
Their lunch buffet rocks! Very fresh food!  Everything here that I have ever had is delicious!
Try their chai. It is amazing!
Try their garlic naan! It is delicious!
Try their naans all of them rule!
Best chicken tikka masala in this part of the valley!
Their buffet lunch is amazing! And hot chai and naan included!!
Everyone here is very friendly; and you feel right at home. The food is amazing! Me and my husband love coming here for lunch and diner!
Try the stuffed shrimp, amazingly delicious!
